-- Total, CPI Plan to Build $4.2 Billion Petrochemical Plant, Tribune Reports
-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 2010-11-03T07:30:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/total-cpi-to-build-2-8-4-2-billion-petrochemical-unit-la-tribune-says.html
Total SA will sign a letter of intent
with Chinese energy group CPI to build a petrochemicals plant
for between 2 billion euros and 3 billion euros, La Tribune
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Total would be a minority partner in the project, according
to the French daily newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  